HEADWORD: Winterkill
<hw>Win"ter*kill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Winterkilled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Winterkilling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To kill by the
cold, or exposure to the inclemency of winter; <as>as, the wheat was
<ex>winterkilled</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winterkill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Winterkill
<hw>Win"ter*kill`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To die as the result of
exposure to the cold of winter; <as>as, the tree <ex>winterkills</ex>
easily</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winterly</ent>⟦br⟧
